        "successLines": [
          {
            "id": "p2-aid-1",
            "text": "Mutual aid stops being an idea and becomes a rhythm. Bowls are filled before anyone asks, shifts are covered without bargaining, and repairs happen quietly at the edge of the foundry lights. Nobody calls it worship — they just call it what you do for each other.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [
              "insight"
            ],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-aid-2",
            "text": "You give Boldrei’s hearth a shape that fits this place: not walls and doors, but promises kept. A simple rite — shared food, shared watch, shared care — becomes something they repeat even when you aren’t there to lead it.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [
              "jtKhCZYpTGESAvVA"
            ],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-pressure-1",
            "text": "Pressure arrives the way it always does in the Cogs: warnings disguised as safety concerns, lost hours, ‘random’ inspections. The circle doesn’t scatter. Someone always shows up anyway. Someone always stands in the doorway.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [
              "ene3aWYathaGoLcl"
            ],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-pressure-2",
            "text": "You learn to feel the stress lines before they crack. You spot the quiet fractures — envy, fear, exhaustion, ideology sharpening into accusation — and you give the group a way to breathe before it breaks. The movement survives because it learns how to bend.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [
              "ne1tTHfgj00arjje"
            ],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-stability-1",
            "text": "The hearth holds through a hard week. Someone who would have slept alone is brought inside the circle. Someone who would have been punished is covered for. The Cogs remain brutal — but in this corner, people are harder to disappear.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [
              "w6XAeyF6UW9kqKCq"
            ],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-stability-2",
            "text": "They don’t just endure; they organize. A few warforged take responsibility without being asked — distributing food, keeping watch, settling disputes. Boldrei’s warmth becomes something practical: a shield they share, not a promise they wait for.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [
              "TJEWJ3dOI4M9IoYX"
            ],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          }
        ],
        "failureLines": [
          {
            "id": "p2-fail-1",
            "text": "The week drains everyone. People still believe, but exhaustion makes them quiet. The hearth doesn’t go out — it just burns low.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-fail-2",
            "text": "An argument over tactics steals the air from the room: comfort versus confrontation, patience versus pressure. No one leaves forever, but the circle feels smaller for a while.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2-fail-3",
            "text": "Pressure lands somewhere tender — a missed shift, a docked ration, a sudden inspection. The community learns the cost again, and moves more carefully for now.",
            "dependsOnChecks": [],
            "dependsOnGroups": []
          }
        ]
      },
